        "title": "feat: add recurring card scheduler",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds first-class recurring cards through the existing card/run scheduler. This keeps cadence in durable D1 state and avoids long-running loops or ad-hoc cron jobs.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds a strict interval schedule contract with bounded cadence and constant-time catch-up.\n- Persists next/last occurrence evidence plus a recoverable five-minute claim lease.\n- Atomically claims due occurrences in bounded batches; concurrent ticks cannot duplicate a run.\n- Coalesces active/capacity-blocked occurrences and isolates per-card dispatch failures so one card cannot starve the batch.\n- Wires the scheduler into the Worker cron and an owner-only manual tick endpoint.\n- Documents the API, scheduler behavior, and operational semantics.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm test`: 621 passed.\n- `pnpm check`: typecheck, lint, and formatting passed.\n- `pnpm build`: passed.\n- Autoreview: clean after fixing dispatch-failure isolation.\n- Disposable local D1: all 28 migrations applied, including upgrade preservation of an existing card.\n- Live local Worker/D1 E2E: authenticated card creation; one due occurrence claimed and queued; cadence advanced; claim lease cleared; second tick scanned zero; run and event evidence persisted.\n- Existing Chrome profile: board rendered the recurring card and queued run with no console warnings or errors.\n",
